---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'; import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro'; import Subnav from '../components/Subnav.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Logo — Leicester Space Week brand"><PageHero eyebrow="Logo system" title="A civic mark for space." intro="The logo brings together an outline fox, a subtle orbit and Leicester’s skyline. It is the clearest expression of the Leicester Space Week identity." /><Subnav items={['Primary logo','Clear space','Minimum size','Incorrect use']} />
<section id="primary-logo" class="section"><div class="shell"><div class="section-head"><p class="eyebrow">Primary logo</p><h2>Use it with intent.</h2><p>The primary stacked logo is our preferred signature for official communications, campaign covers, large-format print and high-impact digital spaces.</p></div><div class="showcase"><div class="logo-field"><img src="/assets/logos/LeicesterSpaceWeek_Icon_Reference.png" alt="Primary Leicester Space Week logo" /></div><div class="showcase-copy"><div><p class="eyebrow">Approved colours</p><h3>On light backgrounds</h3><p>Use the full-colour mark on Paper White or light neutral backgrounds. Do not add effects, outlines or a container.</p></div><a class="button light" href="/assets/logos/LeicesterSpaceWeek_Primary_Reference.png" download>Download PNG</a></div></div></div></section>
<section id="clear-space" class="section" style="background:#e5e1d7"><div class="shell"><div class="section-head"><p class="eyebrow">Clear space</p><h2>Give the crest room.</h2><p>Keep a clear area around the logo equal to the height of the “L” in Leicester. This area must be free of type, imagery and competing marks.</p></div><div class="measure"><img style="width:210px;margin:auto" src="/assets/logos/LeicesterSpaceWeek_Primary_Reference.png" alt="" /><p style="margin-top:22px">X = cap height of the wordmark</p></div></div></section>
<section id="minimum-size" class="section"><div class="shell"><div class="section-head"><p class="eyebrow">Minimum size</p><h2>Stay legible.</h2></div><div class="cards"><article class="card"><span class="glyph">120</span><div><h3>Digital</h3><p>Use the primary logo no smaller than 120 px wide. For tighter spaces, use a simplified icon mark.</p></div></article><article class="card"><span class="glyph">25</span><div><h3>Print</h3><p>Use the primary logo no smaller than 25 mm wide. Keep fine skyline details crisp in production.</p></div></article><article class="card"><span class="glyph">32</span><div><h3>Icon</h3><p>The mark-only icon may be used at 32 px or 10 mm minimum, including for avatars and favicons.</p></div></article></div></div></section>
<section id="incorrect-use" class="section" style="background:#fff"><div class="shell"><div class="section-head"><p class="eyebrow">Incorrect use</p><h2>Keep it precise.</h2></div><div class="usage"><article class="usage-panel do"><span class="check">✓</span><h3>Use approved colourways</h3><p>Use the full-colour version on a light field or the reverse version on Orbit Navy.</p></article><article class="usage-panel dont"><span class="cross">×</span><h3>Never decorate the logo</h3><p>Do not stretch, rotate, recolour, add gradients, shadows, borders or busy imagery behind the mark.</p></article></div></div></section></BaseLayout>
